1
00:00:04,463 --> 00:00:06,298
Long time no see, Kasuga.

2
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:10,760
I guess it's been...
three years now?

3
00:00:10,761 --> 00:00:13,095
It's so crazy bumping into you like this!

4
00:00:13,096 --> 00:00:14,347
Ah...

5
00:00:14,348 --> 00:00:15,474
Yeah.

6
00:00:16,600 --> 00:00:17,809
- Nanako?
- Yes?

7
00:00:18,310 --> 00:00:19,393
Who is this?

8
00:00:19,394 --> 00:00:21,939
Just a classmate from junior high.

9
00:00:23,524 --> 00:00:27,944
I'm on my way to a concert
with my boyfriend. Aren't we?

10
00:00:27,945 --> 00:00:29,695
Yep.

11
00:00:29,696 --> 00:00:30,780
I see...

12
00:00:30,781 --> 00:00:31,782
Ah.

13
00:00:32,282 --> 00:00:33,407
Hey, I know.

14
00:00:33,408 --> 00:00:35,494
Let's exchange contact info.

15
00:00:35,994 --> 00:00:37,453
Sure.

16
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:38,747
Let me see...

17
00:00:42,292 --> 00:00:43,293
There we go.

18
00:00:44,127 --> 00:00:45,629
I'll send a text just in case.

19
00:00:47,756 --> 00:00:48,966
Sent.

20
00:00:53,929 --> 00:00:55,012
Good.

21
00:00:55,013 --> 00:00:56,640
CAN WE TALK? HOW'S THIS WEEKEND?

22
00:00:57,557 --> 00:00:59,017
See you around, then.

23
00:00:59,977 --> 00:01:01,979
- Let's go.
-  Sure.

24
00:02:03,874 --> 00:02:06,208
THE FLOWERS OF EVIL

25
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:09,712
EPISODE 10

26
00:02:16,845 --> 00:02:17,928
Hi ya!

27
00:02:20,766 --> 00:02:22,934
I'm so sleepy.

28
00:02:23,518 --> 00:02:25,853
I couldn't fall asleep at all last night.

29
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:28,148
I ended up working on the prologue.

30
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:30,150
Nice.

31
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,153
The thing is,

32
00:02:34,154 --> 00:02:35,572
I want to ask for a favor.

33
00:02:41,036 --> 00:02:44,330
I've decided not to read other books
until I finish writing mine.

34
00:02:44,331 --> 00:02:46,541
So, I want you to hold on to this for me.

35
00:02:52,756 --> 00:02:56,927
Kasuga, did something happen between you
and that girl we met last night?

36
00:02:58,011 --> 00:03:00,137
Not really...

37
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:02,181
We were just in the same homeroom class.

38
00:03:06,937 --> 00:03:09,356
Okay, then. I'll keep this safe.

39
00:03:21,034 --> 00:03:22,284
What's wrong with you?

40
00:03:22,285 --> 00:03:23,369
I know.

41
00:03:23,370 --> 00:03:27,457
Did I upset your girlfriend
by suggesting we meet?

42
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:32,044
Tokiwa and I aren't dating or anything.

43
00:03:32,045 --> 00:03:33,338
You're not?

44
00:03:36,007 --> 00:03:39,886
Look, they have pizza, too!
So many choices.

45
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:49,771
The food's great, isn't it?

46
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:52,899
Saeki,

47
00:03:54,901 --> 00:03:57,446
how have you been doing... since then?

48
00:03:58,113 --> 00:04:01,241
I don't
remember very well.

49
00:04:01,825 --> 00:04:04,368
I was in Juvenile Detention
for about a month,

50
00:04:04,369 --> 00:04:07,914
and then we moved to Utsunomiya.

51
00:04:09,207 --> 00:04:10,959
But, really, I don't remember much.

52
00:04:11,710 --> 00:04:16,297
I've made friends in high school, though.

53
00:04:16,298 --> 00:04:18,008
I have a boyfriend now, too.

54
00:04:18,717 --> 00:04:19,759
So...

55
00:04:20,510 --> 00:04:22,471
I guess I'm happy and stuff.

56
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:25,347
I see.

57
00:04:25,348 --> 00:04:26,349
Yeah.

58
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:29,478
How about you, Kasuga?

59
00:04:31,188 --> 00:04:32,272
After what happened...

60
00:04:32,773 --> 00:04:34,149
How have you been doing?

61
00:04:39,863 --> 00:04:41,156
Kasuga,

62
00:04:42,866 --> 00:04:44,367
are you happy right now?

63
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:47,871
What about Nakamura?

64
00:04:49,331 --> 00:04:50,332
After that...

65
00:04:51,875 --> 00:04:53,084
How has she been doing?

66
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,004
I don't know.

67
00:04:57,339 --> 00:04:58,882
I haven't seen her since.

68
00:05:01,051 --> 00:05:02,844
I don't even know where she is now.

69
00:05:06,556 --> 00:05:07,557
Why?

70
00:05:10,852 --> 00:05:13,271
Why don't you know
what happened to Nakamura?

71
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:22,155
You were trying to die together, right?

72
00:05:23,365 --> 00:05:26,701
But Nakamura pushed you away.

73
00:05:27,869 --> 00:05:30,372
That's what it looked like to me.
Am I wrong?

74
00:05:30,997 --> 00:05:33,250
Why do you think she did that?

75
00:05:33,792 --> 00:05:36,086
Why did Nakamura shove you, Kasuga?

76
00:05:37,546 --> 00:05:38,964
Don't you know?

77
00:05:42,968 --> 00:05:44,052
When I saw that...

78
00:05:45,595 --> 00:05:48,348
I thought, "Serves you right."

79
00:05:49,641 --> 00:05:52,351
Watching you two fail to die,

80
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:54,436
being forced to live miserably...

81
00:05:54,437 --> 00:05:56,314
I started laughing uncontrollably.

82
00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:59,609
If you two had died that day,

83
00:06:00,193 --> 00:06:01,902
I would have been so frustrated,

84
00:06:01,903 --> 00:06:03,822
I might have lost my mind.

85
00:06:05,949 --> 00:06:07,158
I...

86
00:06:07,826 --> 00:06:09,077
I...

87
00:06:10,954 --> 00:06:12,163
Even though I did that...

88
00:06:13,248 --> 00:06:14,875
I don't feel like dying anymore.

89
00:06:19,796 --> 00:06:21,548
Tokiwa, was it?

90
00:06:23,258 --> 00:06:24,593
Do you...

91
00:06:25,135 --> 00:06:26,177
like her?

92
00:06:28,889 --> 00:06:30,140
I...

93
00:06:32,017 --> 00:06:34,561
I want to read the novel she writes.

94
00:06:35,854 --> 00:06:39,524
She let me read the plot,
and it was really interesting.

95
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:42,569
She's writing that novel now,

96
00:06:43,737 --> 00:06:45,739
- and I...
- Liar.

97
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:50,368
Are you going to make her miserable, too?

98
00:06:53,163 --> 00:06:55,165
She's a replacement for Nakamura.

99
00:06:56,249 --> 00:06:58,208
A tool to make you feel better.

100
00:06:58,209 --> 00:06:59,585
You're wrong.

101
00:06:59,586 --> 00:07:01,086
You haven't changed at all.

102
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:03,297
You use people any way you please,

103
00:07:03,298 --> 00:07:05,382
and throw them out
when it becomes too much.

104
00:07:08,219 --> 00:07:09,679
That's not true.

105
00:07:16,811 --> 00:07:17,896
It is.

106
00:07:19,022 --> 00:07:20,315
Just watch.

107
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:22,692
I know,

108
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:25,445
because that girl isn't Nakamura.

109
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:29,490
You can't face anyone other than Nakamura.

110
00:07:29,491 --> 00:07:31,742
So, you end up having to throw them out.

111
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:36,456
Then again...

112
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:41,169
You never actually faced Nakamura either,
did you?

113
00:07:44,297 --> 00:07:46,800
You just kept running away the whole time.

114
00:07:47,592 --> 00:07:49,761
Running away from everything.

115
00:07:51,513 --> 00:07:53,014
I knew.

116
00:07:53,932 --> 00:07:55,642
I knew that would happen.

117
00:07:57,143 --> 00:07:58,269
Still...

118
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:02,232
I'm disappointed.

119
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:13,743
Excuse me, I'd like to pay now.

120
00:08:55,827 --> 00:08:58,538
KOJI

121
00:09:14,345 --> 00:09:16,890
Were you busy this weekend?

122
00:09:17,432 --> 00:09:20,185
You didn't take any of my calls.

123
00:09:22,937 --> 00:09:24,606
Was it about the novel?

124
00:09:26,858 --> 00:09:28,860
Once I started writing, I dunno...

125
00:09:29,444 --> 00:09:31,654
There wasn't much there, I guess.

126
00:09:33,364 --> 00:09:34,491
I'm disappointed.

127
00:09:35,325 --> 00:09:37,285
I didn't know my writing was this bad.

128
00:09:38,161 --> 00:09:39,496
Don't say that.

129
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:45,627
Actually...

130
00:09:47,337 --> 00:09:51,299
Koji's been asking to make up,

131
00:09:51,800 --> 00:09:55,512
and he says
he also wants to apologize to you, Kasuga.

132
00:09:57,806 --> 00:10:00,975
But, you don't want
to see him again... right?

133
00:10:03,978 --> 00:10:05,313
I'm sorry for the other day!

134
00:10:06,147 --> 00:10:07,397
I was out of line.

135
00:10:07,398 --> 00:10:10,568
Koji, please keep it down.

136
00:10:11,402 --> 00:10:13,237
No, I'm the one who should--

137
00:10:13,238 --> 00:10:14,530
No!

138
00:10:14,531 --> 00:10:17,033
I'm really sorry
for saying those nasty things.

139
00:10:17,784 --> 00:10:19,119
To be honest, that day,

140
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:21,703
I thought you might take Aya from me,

141
00:10:21,704 --> 00:10:23,414
and that's all I could think about.

142
00:10:23,998 --> 00:10:25,792
I'm sorry to you, too, Aya!

143
00:10:26,292 --> 00:10:27,876
- I'll change!
- Hey, Koji?

144
00:10:27,877 --> 00:10:28,878
Can you just...

145
00:10:29,796 --> 00:10:30,839
Ah...

146
00:10:33,716 --> 00:10:37,428
If anything, I feel more confident
after overcoming this crisis with you.

147
00:10:38,388 --> 00:10:41,098
Really? Did you learn your lesson?

148
00:10:41,099 --> 00:10:42,600
I swear!

149
00:10:45,061 --> 00:10:47,605
Could you... accept my apology?

150
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:58,116
I really appreciate it!

151
00:11:00,451 --> 00:11:01,785
- I'll call you!
-  See you.

152
00:11:01,786 --> 00:11:03,829
- You too, Kasuga! See you around.
-  Sure.

153
00:11:03,830 --> 00:11:05,164
Koji, over here.

154
00:11:05,165 --> 00:11:06,958
- Get back to work, please.
-  Ah.

155
00:11:13,631 --> 00:11:15,049
Kasuga,

156
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,387
you must think...

157
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,723
I'm an idiot, right?

158
00:11:23,266 --> 00:11:24,267
What?

159
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:26,144
Why would you say that?

160
00:11:29,147 --> 00:11:31,274
No reason.

161
00:11:35,695 --> 00:11:36,905
Tokiwa!

162
00:11:40,992 --> 00:11:41,993
What is it?

163
00:11:45,246 --> 00:11:46,289
Sorry.

164
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:48,625
It's nothing. Forget it.

165
00:11:57,800 --> 00:12:00,385
DECEMBER 24TH

166
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:03,222
It's December 24th.
What comes to mind?

167
00:12:03,223 --> 00:12:04,473
Santa!

168
00:12:04,474 --> 00:12:06,058
Snow!

169
00:12:06,059 --> 00:12:07,601
Reindeer!

170
00:12:07,602 --> 00:12:09,019
Sleighs!

171
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,646
Presents!

172
00:12:10,647 --> 00:12:12,232
Fir tree!

173
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,069
Aya!

174
00:12:17,070 --> 00:12:18,779
You're so loud.

175
00:12:18,780 --> 00:12:21,199
Why did you come through the gate?

176
00:12:22,492 --> 00:12:25,036
I'm tired of waiting!

177
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:28,580
Why do you have work today,
of all days?

178
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:30,541
I told you.

179
00:12:56,401 --> 00:12:59,445
You haven't changed a bit.

180
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:05,285
You don't actually want
to read Tokiwa's novel.

181
00:13:05,994 --> 00:13:09,080
You just want to be the person
who got to read it.

182
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:13,209
Isn't that right?

183
00:13:14,377 --> 00:13:15,837
That's not true.

184
00:13:16,629 --> 00:13:18,756
You're just like a parasite.

185
00:13:19,674 --> 00:13:21,342
It used to be on books,

186
00:13:21,926 --> 00:13:23,010
then on Saeki,

187
00:13:23,011 --> 00:13:24,262
then on Nakamura.

188
00:13:25,096 --> 00:13:26,681
And next,

189
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:30,018
you're going to use Tokiwa and her novel
for yourself.

190
00:13:30,518 --> 00:13:31,561
You're wrong!

191
00:13:32,103 --> 00:13:35,106
Then why did
Nakamura shove you away?

192
00:13:36,691 --> 00:13:38,109
Why do you not understand?

193
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:42,613
It's because you didn't try
to face anybody!

194
00:13:44,157 --> 00:13:46,242
You're the one who destroyed it all.

195
00:13:47,618 --> 00:13:48,870
You destroyed Saeki,

196
00:13:49,454 --> 00:13:50,705
you destroyed your family,

197
00:13:51,456 --> 00:13:53,373
and you destroyed Nakamura, too.

198
00:14:04,302 --> 00:14:05,470
That's not true...

199
00:14:06,054 --> 00:14:08,598
The person Nakamura was back then is gone.

200
00:14:12,018 --> 00:14:13,227
She doesn't exist

201
00:14:14,771 --> 00:14:16,272
anywhere in this world.

202
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:19,066
It's true.

203
00:14:19,067 --> 00:14:20,318
It's all true.

204
00:14:21,611 --> 00:14:22,612
I...

205
00:14:23,112 --> 00:14:28,076
hurt and broke Nakamura and everyone else.

206
00:14:29,035 --> 00:14:31,913
I might never be forgiven for what I did.

207
00:14:33,206 --> 00:14:34,624
But, still...

208
00:14:35,583 --> 00:14:39,420
Still, the person I need to be facing now,
in this moment, is...

209
00:14:43,174 --> 00:14:44,926
Kasuga,

210
00:14:49,847 --> 00:14:51,432
you must think...

211
00:14:52,058 --> 00:14:53,684
I'm an idiot, right?

212
00:14:56,687 --> 00:14:57,855
Tokiwa,

213
00:15:00,525 --> 00:15:03,236
you've been suffering all alone.

214
00:15:05,029 --> 00:15:06,155
This whole time,

215
00:15:07,073 --> 00:15:08,866
you've suppressed your true self...

216
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:21,170
I can't do that.

217
00:15:22,338 --> 00:15:26,509
I can't keep living
in the world as a ghost!

218
00:15:52,660 --> 00:15:54,078
Here you go.

219
00:15:59,125 --> 00:16:01,502
- Welcome!
-  Welcome!

220
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:09,135
Tokiwa...

221
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:14,849
I love you!

222
00:16:15,683 --> 00:16:17,518
Please go out with me!

223
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:26,986
Hey!

224
00:16:27,486 --> 00:16:31,365
What kind of joke is this?
And on Christmas Eve, of all days?

225
00:16:32,950 --> 00:16:34,910
Calm down for a minute. Have a seat.

226
00:16:34,911 --> 00:16:35,912
Tokiwa.

227
00:16:37,747 --> 00:16:39,123
Wait a second.

228
00:16:39,874 --> 00:16:41,750
I'm on the clock right now.

229
00:16:41,751 --> 00:16:43,502
I'll be taking a break soon, so...

230
00:16:44,086 --> 00:16:45,213
Tokiwa.

231
00:16:46,881 --> 00:16:48,382
Come to me.

232
00:16:49,884 --> 00:16:51,302
I want you in my life!

233
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:55,181
I'll kill your ghost for you.

234
00:16:55,932 --> 00:16:57,224
Let's get off

235
00:16:57,225 --> 00:16:58,768
these tracks.

236
00:17:03,397 --> 00:17:04,982
I'm in love with you!

237
00:17:06,943 --> 00:17:09,445
Seriously, what's gotten into you?

238
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:13,574
Sorry for the commotion, everyone.

239
00:17:14,242 --> 00:17:16,077
- Hey.
- Tokiwa.

240
00:17:16,827 --> 00:17:18,578
- Tokiwa!
-  Drop it already!

241
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:19,664
You're causing trouble!

242
00:17:20,164 --> 00:17:21,415
Koji...

243
00:17:24,669 --> 00:17:25,753
I'm sorry.

244
00:17:26,754 --> 00:17:27,837
What?

245
00:17:29,549 --> 00:17:30,550
What?

246
00:17:31,175 --> 00:17:33,427
What do you mean by "sorry"?

247
00:17:37,807 --> 00:17:38,808
Manager...

248
00:17:39,517 --> 00:17:41,143
- What?
-  I'm sorry.

249
00:17:41,852 --> 00:17:43,478
I'll be quitting as of today.

250
00:17:43,479 --> 00:17:45,273
What the... Quit? Aya?

251
00:18:10,423 --> 00:18:11,465
Manager...

252
00:18:13,801 --> 00:18:15,636
Do you mind if I go on break?

253
00:18:47,043 --> 00:18:49,795
I forgot my bag.

254
00:18:54,759 --> 00:18:56,052
And this apron...

255
00:18:56,844 --> 00:18:58,804
I'll have to wash it and give it back.

256
00:19:02,391 --> 00:19:03,392
Sorry...

257
00:19:55,736 --> 00:19:56,946
So warm.

258
00:20:17,425 --> 00:20:20,302
FINAL CHAPTER

259
00:20:27,476 --> 00:20:28,727
Kasuga!

260
00:20:28,728 --> 00:20:31,105
I didn't look, I promise!

261
00:20:31,731 --> 00:20:33,774
When do I get to read it, though?

262
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:35,734
Soon.

263
00:20:35,735 --> 00:20:37,902
Just as soon as I'm done writing.

264
00:21:05,723 --> 00:21:07,099
Beautiful, isn't it?

265
00:21:09,602 --> 00:21:10,644
Yeah.

266
00:21:13,522 --> 00:21:14,899
Is it really okay?

267
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:18,736
Is it really okay for me to be this happy?

268
00:21:20,029 --> 00:21:21,113
What was that?

269
00:21:22,114 --> 00:21:23,991
I'm happy too, you know?

270
00:21:31,248 --> 00:21:32,291
That reminds me.

271
00:21:32,833 --> 00:21:35,461
There's somewhere I want to go
during spring break.

272
00:21:36,587 --> 00:21:37,588
Where?

273
00:21:38,464 --> 00:21:40,716
The town you were born in.

274
00:21:41,509 --> 00:21:43,093
I want to see it.

275
00:21:45,179 --> 00:21:46,764
There's nothing to see.

276
00:21:47,264 --> 00:21:49,975
It's just a plain old, rural town.

277
00:22:01,904 --> 00:22:02,905
Hello?

278
00:22:04,698 --> 00:22:06,491
Welcome home.

279
00:22:06,492 --> 00:22:07,660
Welcome home.

280
00:22:10,871 --> 00:22:13,540
Grandpa's been taken to the hospital?

281
00:22:13,541 --> 00:22:16,585
It's not looking too good.
Mom and I will go see him tomorrow.

282
00:22:18,504 --> 00:22:20,506
You can stay here, Takao.

283
00:22:46,740 --> 00:22:47,908
I'm coming with you.

284
00:22:48,409 --> 00:22:50,827
TO BE CONTINUED

285
00:23:47,885 --> 00:23:49,010
ON THE NEXT EPISODE

286
00:23:49,011 --> 00:23:52,722
Kasuga is dragged back
to his past after seeing Saeki again.

287
00:23:52,723 --> 00:23:55,558
He visits his hometown
for the first time in three years.

288
00:23:55,559 --> 00:23:57,269
Next, on Episode 11,

289
00:23:58,020 --> 00:24:01,814
Kasuga finally finds a lead
that could help him find Nakamura.

290
00:24:01,815 --> 00:24:02,816
Translated by Yuka Kristi
